00:27:09,777 --> 00:27:13,850
Do you know you
have a special aura?

268
00:27:14,417 --> 00:27:17,727
You're so young,
but you have
the bone structure

269
00:27:17,897 --> 00:27:21,128
and chi flow
of a kung-fu genius.

270
00:27:21,697 --> 00:27:25,736
If your chi flow
can be channelled,
then you will be invincible!

271
00:27:25,897 --> 00:27:29,287
Like the old saying:
You cannot escape your destiny.

272
00:27:29,777 --> 00:27:34,328
The duty of upholding
world peace and punishing
evil will be yours.

273
00:27:34,897 --> 00:27:35,886
Sure.

274
00:27:36,737 --> 00:27:40,013
This is the scroll of the
Buddhist Palm. It's priceless.

275
00:27:40,177 --> 00:27:43,567
But as it's fate,
I'll let you have it for $10.

276
00:27:43,817 --> 00:27:45,136
[###]

277
00:27:45,817 --> 00:27:47,728
BUDDHIST PALM MANU AL

278
00:27:51,537 --> 00:27:53,971
You gave him your life savings?
Yes.

279
00:27:54,137 --> 00:27:57,288
I was saving to study to be
a doctor or lawyer,

280
00:27:57,457 --> 00:27:59,732
but this was world peace.

281
00:28:05,657 --> 00:28:06,885
[CHATTERING]

282
00:28:22,777 --> 00:28:25,007
SING:
Let go of the girl!

283
00:28:43,057 --> 00:28:45,776
Hey! It's the Buddhist Palm!

284
00:28:46,097 --> 00:28:47,530
"The 20-Cent Kung Fu Manual."

285
00:28:47,697 --> 00:28:48,766
[CHILDREN LAUGHING]

286
00:28:48,937 --> 00:28:50,006
You must be loaded.

287
00:28:50,417 --> 00:28:52,487
Have you killed anyone lately?

288
00:29:03,297 --> 00:29:08,007
He's a fool,
and she's mute.
Losers!

289
00:29:09,697 --> 00:29:13,372
I realized then that good guys
never win. I want to be bad.

290
00:29:14,177 --> 00:29:16,168
I want to be the killer!

291
00:29:17,457 --> 00:29:19,527
Ice cream!
Where?

292
00:29:20,337 --> 00:29:22,009
Make mine a vanilla.

293
00:29:22,177 --> 00:29:23,496
Chocolate for me!

294
00:29:26,177 --> 00:29:27,610
[###]

295
00:29:34,577 --> 00:29:37,455
What're you looking at?
Never seen free
ice cream before?

296
00:29:42,657 --> 00:29:43,806
Look at her run!

297
00:29:44,017 --> 00:29:45,450
[LAUGHING]

298
00:29:58,497 --> 00:30:03,617
You're such kung-fu masters,
go take it on the road.

299
00:30:03,777 --> 00:30:06,007
You belong
in the circus, not here!

300
00:30:06,177 --> 00:30:10,250
Don't say that, Landlady.
There must be
a reason they're here.

301
00:30:10,537 --> 00:30:12,812
Everyone has
his reasons.

302
00:30:12,977 --> 00:30:14,968
We don't want
to make trouble.

303
00:30:15,137 --> 00:30:17,731
I'm glad you get it.
The mob's mad at us.

304
00:30:17,897 --> 00:30:20,889
We'll never hear the end of it.
Why don't you get lost!

305
00:30:21,937 --> 00:30:23,848
Your wife shouldn't be so nasty.

306
00:30:24,017 --> 00:30:25,336
[MOANS]

307
00:30:26,257 --> 00:30:28,009
You okay?

308
00:30:29,897 --> 00:30:31,376
WOMAN:
Masters.

309
00:30:38,657 --> 00:30:40,568
We have nothing
precious to give you,

310
00:30:40,737 --> 00:30:42,967
but take this as a token
of our appreciation.

311
00:30:43,817 --> 00:30:45,614
Thanks for saving us!

312
00:30:53,057 --> 00:30:54,172
LANDLAD Y:
Stop the crying.

313
00:30:54,337 --> 00:30:55,929
This isn't a show!

314
00:30:56,097 --> 00:30:59,533
You're so cold-hearted.
Talking back to me, eh?

315
00:30:59,697 --> 00:31:02,370
You may know kung fu,
but you're still a fairy.

316
00:31:02,777 --> 00:31:04,130
[CRYING]

317
00:31:04,777 --> 00:31:07,530
It's no crime to be
good at kung fu!

318
00:31:07,697 --> 00:31:10,370
Once a fairy,
always a fairy.

319
00:31:10,537 --> 00:31:13,927
Look at you. What's with
the red underwear?

320
00:31:14,097 --> 00:31:16,486
Why not a diaper
while you're at it.

321
00:31:17,697 --> 00:31:19,653
J ANE:
What's wrong
with red underwear?

322
00:31:19,857 --> 00:31:22,576
Where were you
when there was trouble?

323
00:31:22,737 --> 00:31:26,571
If it weren't for them,
we'd be finished.
Be reasonable!

324
00:31:26,737 --> 00:31:28,170
I'll reason with you.

325
00:31:28,337 --> 00:31:31,454
You owe me three
months' rent. That's $90.

326
00:31:31,617 --> 00:31:33,767
Pay up or pack up!

327
00:31:33,937 --> 00:31:36,007
Don't you worry. I'll pay it.

328
00:31:36,177 --> 00:31:38,566
Think you're a smartass,
Rabbit-Tooth Jane?

329
00:31:38,737 --> 00:31:41,297
What's it to you,
tub of lard?

330
00:31:41,457 --> 00:31:42,572
Bitch!

331
00:31:43,657 --> 00:31:45,249
Calm down, Landlady.

332
00:31:46,577 --> 00:31:48,329
This is your fault.

333
00:31:48,497 --> 00:31:50,169
[PEOPLE SHOUTING]

334
00:31:50,737 --> 00:31:52,932
MAN 1: Are you trying to kill us?
MAN 2: You're right.

335
00:31:53,097 --> 00:31:55,167
MAN 3:
How could you do that?

336
00:31:55,337 --> 00:31:57,168
Shut the hell up!

337
00:31:57,377 --> 00:31:59,095
[HIGH-PITCHED SCREAMING]

338
00:31:59,297 --> 00:32:00,286
[GLASS SHATTERS]

339
00:32:09,777 --> 00:32:11,927
You think you can out-yell me?

340
00:32:15,857 --> 00:32:18,530
The fat lady can really sing.

341
00:32:19,537 --> 00:32:20,970
Watch this!

342
00:32:31,217 --> 00:32:32,775
[###]

343
00:32:35,297 --> 00:32:36,446
What happened?

344
00:32:36,817 --> 00:32:39,615
What do you mean,
what happened? You try it.

345
00:32:39,777 --> 00:32:41,654
Me?
Quick!

346
00:32:47,217 --> 00:32:49,412
Sorry! You okay?

347
00:32:50,137 --> 00:32:53,254
I think you should get closer
and take better aim. Okay?

348
00:32:53,417 --> 00:32:54,452
Okay!

349
00:33:06,177 --> 00:33:08,737
Who's throwing the handles?
Handle?

350
00:33:10,777 --> 00:33:12,654
Where's the third knife?

351
00:33:13,297 --> 00:33:15,652
God knows where it went.

352
00:33:15,817 --> 00:33:18,172
Could it be the
same one? Can't be...

353
00:33:18,337 --> 00:33:20,009
Don't!
Sorry.

354
00:33:22,097 --> 00:33:23,849
What are you trying to say?

355
00:33:24,017 --> 00:33:28,010
I just remembered I have
something to do. See you!

356
00:33:30,537 --> 00:33:32,493
Uh-oh. They've seen us!

357
00:33:33,937 --> 00:33:35,336
Stay back!

358
00:33:43,657 --> 00:33:47,570
Don't panic! Snakes like music.
If I whistle, they won't bite.

359
00:33:47,737 --> 00:33:49,250
Please, no more bright ideas.

360
00:33:49,657 --> 00:33:51,534
[HISSING]

361
00:33:53,177 --> 00:33:54,292
Oh, what the hell!

362
00:33:54,457 --> 00:33:55,776
[WHISTLES]

363
00:33:58,697 --> 00:33:59,686
[GASPS]

364
00:34:01,097 --> 00:34:02,576
Not you again, asshole!

365
00:34:02,737 --> 00:34:05,968
MAN:
Get back to your business!

366
00:34:07,737 --> 00:34:09,170
Split up!

367
00:34:11,377 --> 00:34:12,492
Split?

368
00:34:13,177 --> 00:34:14,815
[###]

369
00:34:17,617 --> 00:34:19,414
[WHIRRING]

370
00:34:53,417 --> 00:34:54,645
[HORN HONKING]

371
00:35:05,577 --> 00:35:06,805
[THUD]

372
00:35:18,857 --> 00:35:20,893
[###]

373
00:35:37,137 --> 00:35:38,855
[TYRES SCREECHING]

374
00:35:39,017 --> 00:35:40,336
[WOMEN SCREAM]

375
00:35:45,017 --> 00:35:48,407
[POUNDING]

376
00:36:19,977 --> 00:36:21,251
What're you doing here?

377
00:36:21,417 --> 00:36:23,487
Looking for you.
Weren't you hurt?

378
00:36:23,657 --> 00:36:24,806
I'm fine!

379
00:36:26,777 --> 00:36:29,575
How come you always
recover so fast?

380
00:36:29,897 --> 00:36:31,330
I don't know.

381
00:36:31,697 --> 00:36:34,211
Which hospital did you go to?
Don't remember.

382
00:36:34,937 --> 00:36:36,495
Maybe it's better that way.

383
00:36:36,657 --> 00:36:41,173
Memories can be painful.
To forget may be a blessing!

384
00:36:41,337 --> 00:36:44,056
I never knew
you were so deep.

385
00:36:45,257 --> 00:36:47,646
All the sadness
one can bear...

386
00:36:55,297 --> 00:36:58,414
down the river everywhere.

387
00:37:00,577 --> 00:37:02,090
Hey, get out of the way!

388
00:37:02,257 --> 00:37:03,485
SING'S SIDEKICK:
Move!

389
00:37:03,657 --> 00:37:05,249
SING:
I'll slap you
to kingdom come!

390
00:37:05,617 --> 00:37:09,292
Look at those four-eyes
carting around a coffin.

391
00:37:11,057 --> 00:37:12,490
What morons!

392
00:37:14,537 --> 00:37:16,607
LANDLAD Y:
Don't blame me
for making you leave.

393
00:37:16,777 --> 00:37:19,132
We'll let Buddha decide

394
00:37:19,297 --> 00:37:21,094
[BELL TOLLING]

395
00:37:21,257 --> 00:37:23,532
whether you stay

396
00:37:23,697 --> 00:37:26,052
or go.

397
00:37:29,777 --> 00:37:31,688
HORRIFICALLY BAD FATE

398
00:37:43,217 --> 00:37:44,889
Have some tea.

399
00:37:51,817 --> 00:37:54,729
We're grateful for
some professional help.

400
00:37:54,897 --> 00:37:58,412
We understand the problem.
Twelve Kicks from the Tam School,

401
00:37:58,577 --> 00:38:03,367
Iron Fist from the Hung School
and the Hexagon Staff...

402
00:38:03,937 --> 00:38:05,848
Those guys at Pig Sty
are really good.

403
00:38:06,017 --> 00:38:08,167
HARPIST 2:
Their warrior days
are long over,

404
00:38:08,657 --> 00:38:11,967
but they're still top fighters.

405
00:38:12,337 --> 00:38:16,967
This job is a great
challenge for us.

406
00:38:17,297 --> 00:38:19,731
Now, that's professionalism.

407
00:38:19,897 --> 00:38:25,017
Number One Killers.
Expensive, yes,
but worth every penny!

408
00:38:25,177 --> 00:38:31,173
No! Number one is the Beast,
the world's top killer.

409
00:38:31,617 --> 00:38:35,735
HARPIST 2:
He was so dedicated to kung fu,
he went crazy.

410
00:38:35,897 --> 00:38:39,048
I heard he's now in an asylum.

411
00:38:39,657 --> 00:38:42,808
So you're the
top killers now.

412
00:38:42,977 --> 00:38:47,175
Strictly speaking,
we're just musicians.

413
00:38:47,457 --> 00:38:52,008
A song that wrenches the heart
O where do I find a knowing ear?

414
00:38:52,297 --> 00:38:56,495
Great poem, isn't it?

415
00:38:57,697 --> 00:38:59,574
[###]

416
00:39:04,257 --> 00:39:05,736
We'll be saying
goodbye soon.

417
00:39:05,897 --> 00:39:08,286
Who knows when we'll
see each other again.

418
00:39:08,977 --> 00:39:13,016
We're three of a kind.
Wish we'd known before.

419
00:39:13,177 --> 00:39:16,328
Let's take this opportunity
to spar a little.

420
00:39:16,577 --> 00:39:19,808
No. We still have
a lot to pack.

421
00:39:20,537 --> 00:39:22,209
You're right.

422
00:39:32,617 --> 00:39:34,130
[###]

423
00:39:58,697 --> 00:40:01,894
Twelve Kicks of the Tam School!
Superb attack and defence!

424
00:40:02,097 --> 00:40:04,816
Iron Fist: powerful yet
delicate. Top-notch!

425
00:40:05,057 --> 00:40:08,208
Hexagon Staff, with its
thousand moves. Mystical!

426
00:40:08,657 --> 00:40:10,215
ALL:
Till we meet again!

427
00:40:10,377 --> 00:40:11,651
[SHOUTS]

428
00:40:11,817 --> 00:40:13,648
[CLATTERING & CAT SCREECHING]

429
00:40:15,177 --> 00:40:17,008
[MUSIC PLAYING
ON RECORD PLAYER]

430
00:40:20,177 --> 00:40:21,212
LANDLAD Y:
More lipstick!

431
00:40:26,977 --> 00:40:29,093
[INDISTINCT CHATTERING]

432
00:40:39,737 --> 00:40:42,615
Stay there,
or I'll break you in half.

433
00:41:18,057 --> 00:41:19,854
[###]

434
00:41:30,817 --> 00:41:32,136
[###]

435
00:41:35,417 --> 00:41:36,691
[JINGLE]

436
00:41:42,897 --> 00:41:44,125
[###]

437
00:42:03,097 --> 00:42:05,088
Sorry, we're closed.

438
00:42:05,257 --> 00:42:07,213
You can make
a suit in no time.

439
00:42:07,377 --> 00:42:08,810
We're moving.

440
00:42:08,977 --> 00:42:10,729
This is good material!

441
00:42:11,377 --> 00:42:13,607
You know your stuff.

442
00:42:14,097 --> 00:42:16,167
This has high artistic value.

443
00:42:16,777 --> 00:42:18,051
How high?

444
00:42:18,457 --> 00:42:20,209
At least a few stories...

445
00:43:11,737 --> 00:43:13,295
[###]

446
00:43:27,457 --> 00:43:29,607
Insulting the Axe Gang!
We'll show them.

447
00:43:29,777 --> 00:43:32,814
Let's kill them all and make
this place a brothel.

448
00:43:32,977 --> 00:43:34,888
Don't block my view!

449
00:44:22,377 --> 00:44:23,366
What's going on?

450
00:44:32,257 --> 00:44:33,531
[GRUNTING]

451
00:44:34,337 --> 00:44:35,406
Good!
Good!

452
00:44:35,577 --> 00:44:37,329
Don't block my view!

453
00:44:42,297 --> 00:44:45,334
Damn! I told those nitwits to leave,
but they're still here.

454
00:44:45,497 --> 00:44:47,169
Really?
Yeah.

455
00:45:09,777 --> 00:45:13,611
What the hell is this fighting?
Who'll pay for the damage?

456
00:45:13,777 --> 00:45:15,688
Sorry, sorry. It's nothing!

457
00:46:38,977 --> 00:46:40,205
[COUGHS]

458
00:46:52,217 --> 00:46:55,175
You know what time it is?
I have to sleep.

459
00:46:56,257 --> 00:46:58,088
Hey, fatso, eat shit and die!

460
00:46:58,937 --> 00:47:00,370
Die? In this racket?

461
00:47:00,537 --> 00:47:02,493
Sorry, sorry!

462
00:47:03,017 --> 00:47:04,530
[LAUGHS]

463
00:47:04,697 --> 00:47:06,608
Get out of my way!

464
00:47:07,377 --> 00:47:09,015
Hang in there, Tailor.

465
00:47:17,457 --> 00:47:19,687
LANDLAD Y:
Be quiet!

466
00:47:19,897 --> 00:47:21,410
[HIGH-PITCHED SCREAMING]

467
00:47:24,697 --> 00:47:29,248
LANDLAD Y:
Give us a break!
Why push us so far?

468
00:47:43,337 --> 00:47:44,486
There's another master?

469
00:47:56,217 --> 00:47:57,616
[###]

470
00:48:44,097 --> 00:48:45,246
[GRUNTING]

471
00:48:45,457 --> 00:48:47,175
[GROANING]

472
00:49:39,657 --> 00:49:42,296
[SCREAMING]

473
00:50:03,457 --> 00:50:04,776
[GRUNTING]

474
00:50:05,577 --> 00:50:07,488
It's the Lion's Roar!

475
00:50:08,137 --> 00:50:09,889
I thought that was a myth.

476
00:50:11,057 --> 00:50:13,890
Who knew the Lion's Roar
really exists?

477
00:50:14,057 --> 00:50:17,493
That's the last
we'll see of them.

478
00:50:20,337 --> 00:50:22,771
It's bad, Brother Sum.
Quick, start the car!

479
00:50:23,137 --> 00:50:24,695
Start the car!

480
00:50:31,057 --> 00:50:32,285
Boss!

481
00:50:32,457 --> 00:50:34,607
Keep it down!
Have you no manners?

482
00:50:34,777 --> 00:50:37,086
Get lost. People
are trying to sleep.

483
00:50:37,257 --> 00:50:40,090
They have
to work tomorrow.
Get out of here!

484
00:50:43,217 --> 00:50:44,775
Scumbags!

485
00:51:09,817 --> 00:51:11,808
[###]

486
00:52:02,497 --> 00:52:04,169
[WOMEN SOBBING]

487
00:52:07,097 --> 00:52:10,009
DONUT:
I can't hang on much longer.

488
00:52:12,297 --> 00:52:16,006
But having seen
real masters
like you...

489
00:52:16,697 --> 00:52:18,688
I can now die in peace.

490
00:52:18,857 --> 00:52:20,688
Don't say that.

491
00:52:20,857 --> 00:52:23,690
We're ordinary folks.

492
00:52:23,857 --> 00:52:25,529
Ordinary's a blessing.

493
00:52:25,697 --> 00:52:29,007
Don't call us masters.

494
00:52:29,177 --> 00:52:31,008
But you're such
great fighters!

495
00:52:31,177 --> 00:52:35,250
If only you'd helped earlier,
they wouldn't have to die this way.

496
00:52:35,737 --> 00:52:39,730
Like Donut said,
everyone has his reasons.

497
00:52:40,497 --> 00:52:42,135
Years ago...

498
00:52:42,617 --> 00:52:45,609
we saw our only son
killed in a fight.

499
00:52:47,737 --> 00:52:50,297
Revenge can be devastating.

500
00:52:50,657 --> 00:52:52,727
Do you understand?

501
00:52:52,897 --> 00:52:55,855
Why don't you train us
to be top fighters

502
00:52:56,017 --> 00:52:58,895
and we'll avenge them!

503
00:52:59,057 --> 00:53:03,050
Becoming a top
fighter takes time.

504
00:53:03,217 --> 00:53:05,685
Unless you're
a natural-born
kung-fu genius.

505
00:53:05,857 --> 00:53:09,452
And they're one in a million.

506
00:53:09,657 --> 00:53:11,693
[GRUNTS]

507
00:53:16,737 --> 00:53:18,853
It's obvious I'm the one!

508
00:53:22,257 --> 00:53:24,373
Don't think so.

509
00:53:25,297 --> 00:53:30,451
Everyone! We swore
we'd never fight again.

510
00:53:30,617 --> 00:53:32,926
But we broke that promise today.

511
00:53:33,097 --> 00:53:36,487
For your own safety,
please all leave!

512
00:53:40,777 --> 00:53:44,167
In great power
lies great responsibility.

513
00:53:44,657 --> 00:53:46,454
There's no escaping from it.

514
00:53:46,857 --> 00:53:49,291
Donut, you're hurt bad.

515
00:53:49,457 --> 00:53:50,970
Rest now.

516
00:53:51,177 --> 00:53:52,929
[BABBLING]

517
00:53:55,697 --> 00:53:58,052
We can't understand
what you're saying.

518
00:53:59,457 --> 00:54:00,685
Donut!

519
00:54:06,177 --> 00:54:07,690
[###]

520
00:54:13,217 --> 00:54:15,128
I know you, four-eyes!

521
00:54:16,497 --> 00:54:20,888
You seem prejudiced against
the sight-challenged.

522
00:54:21,057 --> 00:54:24,208
That's right. Especially
gold-framed four-eyes.

523
00:54:24,417 --> 00:54:25,645
[GRUNTING]

524
00:54:25,817 --> 00:54:27,045
[HISSING]

525
00:54:28,297 --> 00:54:31,494
Gold frames
are perfect for clerks.

526
00:54:31,657 --> 00:54:34,615
I think I look good.
So why keep
picking on me?

527
00:54:36,897 --> 00:54:37,886
Help me!

528
00:54:38,377 --> 00:54:39,935
[GROWLING]

529
00:54:40,097 --> 00:54:43,214
"Help me! Help me!"
Want to play, punks?

530
00:54:43,377 --> 00:54:45,129
The Dragon Style?
The Tiger Style?

531
00:54:49,657 --> 00:54:53,935
Come down here,
and I'll smash your
glasses. Come on!

532
00:54:55,537 --> 00:54:57,653
You know I'd do it, right?

533
00:54:58,937 --> 00:55:00,211
Swear to it!

534
00:55:00,817 --> 00:55:02,091
Swear!

535
00:55:04,817 --> 00:55:08,651
Have you no respect?
Where were you
when I needed you?

536
00:55:08,817 --> 00:55:10,045
[BARKS]

537
00:55:10,617 --> 00:55:12,255
You sound like a wimp!

538
00:55:12,417 --> 00:55:15,454
We always get beat!
We haven't gotten anywhere.

539
00:55:15,617 --> 00:55:19,212
No killing, no arson,
no robberies, no rapes...

540
00:55:19,377 --> 00:55:21,811
all because of you!

541
00:55:21,977 --> 00:55:24,207
You're a numb-nut!

542
00:55:26,537 --> 00:55:27,811
Follow me!

543
00:55:36,097 --> 00:55:37,655
It's a stickup!
Where's the money?

544
00:55:42,377 --> 00:55:44,493
Where's the money?

545
00:55:46,017 --> 00:55:48,053
What're you looking at?
I'm serious!

546
00:55:52,817 --> 00:55:56,651
I kill people for less!
Give me the money.

547
00:56:02,857 --> 00:56:04,973
[###]

548
00:56:14,297 --> 00:56:15,889
The money's in here.

549
00:56:50,377 --> 00:56:52,129
SING [AS A CHILD]:
Let go of the girl!

550
00:57:04,617 --> 00:57:09,088
He's a fool,
and she's mute.
Losers!

551
00:57:50,777 --> 00:57:54,053
Go away!
You're dragging me down!

552
00:57:54,777 --> 00:57:59,692
Go home and raise pigs.

553
00:58:04,377 --> 00:58:05,810
Go, before I kill you.

554
00:58:35,337 --> 00:58:37,248
[BAND PLAYING MUSIC]

555
00:58:52,657 --> 00:58:55,888
MAN:
You! Whatsyourname!

556
00:59:04,617 --> 00:59:07,893
Take this and get
some new clothes.
You're now an Axe!

557
00:59:08,057 --> 00:59:11,732
For real?
Someone's waiting for you.

558
00:59:18,377 --> 00:59:19,492
Brother Sum!

559
00:59:19,657 --> 00:59:23,969
One look at you, and I knew
you'd do anything.

560
00:59:24,257 --> 00:59:25,246
Right!

561
00:59:25,497 --> 00:59:27,089
You just needed your chance.

562
00:59:27,857 --> 00:59:28,846
Damn right!

563
00:59:29,017 --> 00:59:30,609
We have an assignment for you.

564
00:59:30,777 --> 00:59:32,290
Anything, Brother Sum!

565
00:59:32,497 --> 00:59:34,169
[###]

566
00:59:50,377 --> 00:59:53,255
SING:
"Research on abnormal people."
What's that?

567
00:59:53,417 --> 00:59:55,135
A mental asylum.

568
00:59:55,337 --> 00:59:57,168
[ALARM BUZZING]

569
01:00:00,657 --> 01:00:01,806
Soldiers!

570
01:00:01,977 --> 01:00:03,649
Boy Scouts!

571
01:00:03,817 --> 01:00:04,806
SING:
Tanks!

572
01:00:04,977 --> 01:00:06,808
ADVISOR:
No worries.

573
01:00:06,977 --> 01:00:10,447
When the Boy Scouts
change shifts, you have
exactly five minutes.

574
01:00:10,617 --> 01:00:14,405
Follow the arrows
on the map.
Go to the last cell

575
01:00:14,577 --> 01:00:19,048
and get the man inside
there out. Here's your tools.

576
01:00:24,697 --> 01:00:26,130
What about you guys?

577
01:00:26,297 --> 01:00:28,208
We're your lookouts.

578
01:00:31,417 --> 01:00:33,169
[WIND WHISTLING]

579
01:00:35,137 --> 01:00:36,809
[THUNDER RUMBLING]

580
01:00:39,177 --> 01:00:41,088
Five minutes. Hurry!

581
01:00:46,017 --> 01:00:47,609
[###]

582
01:01:06,497 --> 01:01:07,976
[GASPS]

583
01:01:19,977 --> 01:01:21,456
[GRUNTS]

584
01:02:18,737 --> 01:02:19,965
[LOCK CLICKS]

585
01:02:32,657 --> 01:02:34,249
[###]

586
01:02:46,737 --> 01:02:48,295
[BROTHER SUM YAWNS]

587
01:02:49,897 --> 01:02:54,527
The world's top killer
indeed looks the part!

588
01:02:55,537 --> 01:02:57,767
It's only a title.

589
01:02:57,937 --> 01:03:01,247
Cut the bullshit.
We want two people killed.
Name your price.

590
01:03:01,777 --> 01:03:03,210
Name my what?

591
01:03:05,497 --> 01:03:10,571
I've killed so many
trying to find
a worthy adversary.

592
01:03:10,897 --> 01:03:14,048
So far, I've never found one.

593
01:03:14,377 --> 01:03:16,129
That's why I stayed inside.

594
01:03:16,297 --> 01:03:20,495
Had I met my match,
I'd have been out long ago.

595
01:03:20,657 --> 01:03:23,046
If you find me
a worthy opponent...

596
01:03:23,217 --> 01:03:25,412
I'll do it for free.
No charge!

597
01:03:25,617 --> 01:03:26,845
[LAUGHING]

598
01:03:27,457 --> 01:03:28,572
Do you have someone?

599
01:03:28,737 --> 01:03:33,765
Yes. Brilliant fighters
who are up to the challenge.

600
01:03:33,937 --> 01:03:36,167
But first, will you
show us some moves?

601
01:03:36,337 --> 01:03:39,249
Not that we don't trust you.
We want to see you in action.

602
01:03:39,617 --> 01:03:43,690
You numskulls aren't worthy!

603
01:03:44,177 --> 01:03:45,405
[SNAPS FINGERS]

604
01:03:48,017 --> 01:03:49,609
He doesn't look the part.

605
01:03:50,497 --> 01:03:55,491
The slippers are a little crappy.
But he'll clean up well.

606
01:03:55,657 --> 01:03:57,454
You sure you
got the right guy?

607
01:03:57,617 --> 01:04:00,814
Absolutely. I swear I did
exactly what you told me.

608
01:04:02,097 --> 01:04:05,885
Please show us some
moves, Mr. Beast.
Don't make it hard for me!

609
01:04:06,057 --> 01:04:07,615
You dumb or what?

610
01:04:08,417 --> 01:04:10,328
You know what
this is, old man?

611
01:04:10,737 --> 01:04:13,092
Ever seen a fist this big?

612
01:04:13,257 --> 01:04:16,249
Don't force me to fight.
I scare myself when I fight!

613
01:04:16,417 --> 01:04:18,248
Really? Try me, then.

614
01:04:21,937 --> 01:04:24,007
Is he okay?

615
01:04:24,977 --> 01:04:26,808
[LAUGHING]

616
01:04:29,577 --> 01:04:32,011
So you say you can fight?

617
01:04:33,217 --> 01:04:34,332
Harder!

618
01:04:34,497 --> 01:04:35,566
[GLASSES SHATTER]

619
01:04:35,737 --> 01:04:36,965
Harder!

620
01:04:39,217 --> 01:04:40,491
Harder!

621
01:04:43,217 --> 01:04:46,573
You hit like that
and call yourself a gangster?

622
01:04:51,337 --> 01:04:52,565
A foreign gun!

623
01:04:52,777 --> 01:04:54,051
[GUNS COCKING]

624
01:05:04,417 --> 01:05:05,691
[GUNSHOT]

625
01:05:11,697 --> 01:05:13,289
[###]

626
01:05:17,177 --> 01:05:22,297
In the world of kung fu,
speed defines the winner.

627
01:05:26,257 --> 01:05:29,010
The Beast is the best of them all.

628
01:05:29,297 --> 01:05:32,812
The Axe Gang extends its respect!

629
01:05:57,897 --> 01:05:59,250
[SCREAMING]

630
01:06:12,857 --> 01:06:15,610
The real masters,
together in one room!

631
01:06:16,657 --> 01:06:20,696
Only the world's top killer

632
01:06:20,857 --> 01:06:22,973
has such an aura.

633
01:06:23,697 --> 01:06:24,925
BEAST:
Likewise.

634
01:06:25,497 --> 01:06:28,057
Could you two be the fated lovers...?

635
01:06:28,217 --> 01:06:29,206
Paris...

636
01:06:29,377 --> 01:06:30,412
And Helen of Troy!

637
01:06:31,177 --> 01:06:32,769
A pleasure, indeed.

638
01:06:33,017 --> 01:06:36,692
We're here to deal
with the Axe Gang...

639
01:06:36,857 --> 01:06:38,415
and only the Axe Gang.

640
01:06:38,577 --> 01:06:40,249
[BROTHER SUM LAUGHING]

641
01:06:40,417 --> 01:06:43,136
You should've killed me before.

642
01:06:43,457 --> 01:06:47,689
Now you're committing suicide.

643
01:06:47,857 --> 01:06:51,054
You're living on borrowed time.

644
01:06:51,217 --> 01:06:54,095
You can't escape your fate!

645
01:06:54,817 --> 01:06:56,887
What's this? A funeral bell?

646
01:06:57,057 --> 01:06:58,092
[SNICKERS]

647
01:06:58,257 --> 01:07:00,976
With the Beast here,
let's see whose funeral it is!

648
01:07:01,777 --> 01:07:03,449
LANDLAD Y:
So you're on their side?

649
01:07:03,617 --> 01:07:05,687
Don't get me wrong.

650
01:07:05,857 --> 01:07:09,293
I only want to kill you...

651
01:07:09,457 --> 01:07:12,255
or be killed by you.

652
01:07:12,457 --> 01:07:14,129
[LAUGHS]

653
01:07:14,657 --> 01:07:16,534
What do you think?

654
01:07:16,697 --> 01:07:21,817
The good cannot coexist
with the bad. You can't
escape your destiny.

655
01:07:22,417 --> 01:07:25,614
So be it. Let's do it.

656
01:07:26,577 --> 01:07:27,930
Okay.

657
01:07:29,057 --> 01:07:30,376
Let's do it!

658
01:07:30,537 --> 01:07:32,016
[###]

659
01:07:49,457 --> 01:07:51,766
Piece of cake. I can handle this.

660
01:07:58,977 --> 01:08:00,649
[BEAST CHUCKLING]

661
01:08:00,817 --> 01:08:03,570
Good try, but a little off target.

662
01:08:18,897 --> 01:08:20,216
[LAUGHING]

663
01:08:30,697 --> 01:08:32,369
[###]

664
01:09:00,777 --> 01:09:03,337
[HIGH-PITCHED SCREAMING]

665
01:09:20,097 --> 01:09:21,689
The Lion's Roar?

666
01:10:23,217 --> 01:10:24,650
[GRUNTING & COUGHING]

667
01:10:31,417 --> 01:10:32,850
[CHIMING]

668
01:11:11,537 --> 01:11:13,209
[HIGH-PITCHED SCREAMING]

669
01:11:18,017 --> 01:11:19,530
[GLASS SHATTERING]

670
01:11:23,817 --> 01:11:25,216
[SCREAMS]

671
01:11:56,017 --> 01:11:57,211
BEAST:
Wait!

672
01:11:58,337 --> 01:12:02,967
I didn't know the Lion's Roar
could be done with a speaker!

673
01:12:03,137 --> 01:12:05,367
What a blow!

674
01:12:13,497 --> 01:12:14,566
[GRUNTING]

675
01:12:33,457 --> 01:12:36,529
Looks like they're not up to it!
Let's get them while they're down.

676
01:12:36,697 --> 01:12:37,766
You do it!

677
01:12:37,937 --> 01:12:39,495
I'm gonna puke!
I need to see a doctor!

678
01:12:39,657 --> 01:12:40,806
Go to hell!

679
01:12:45,017 --> 01:12:46,735
You! Come over here.

680
01:12:47,697 --> 01:12:49,767
Hit him!
Yes!

681
01:12:54,097 --> 01:12:55,894
The head!
Of course!

682
01:12:56,137 --> 01:12:57,775
Hit him on the head!
Okay.

683
01:12:57,937 --> 01:12:59,689
Here's your chance.
Got it!

684
01:12:59,857 --> 01:13:00,926
Hit him!
Hit him!

685
01:13:01,097 --> 01:13:02,530
Hit the shit out of him!
Right!

686
01:13:02,697 --> 01:13:03,891
Hit him!
Hit him!

687
01:13:04,057 --> 01:13:05,775
Beat the shit out of him!

688
01:13:07,697 --> 01:13:08,686
What're you doing?

689
01:13:09,377 --> 01:13:12,175
You want me to hit him
or beat the shit out of him?

690
01:13:12,337 --> 01:13:14,214
You're making me
very confused!

691
01:13:15,457 --> 01:13:17,129
[SCREAMING]

692
01:13:24,417 --> 01:13:25,736
[###]

693
01:13:41,377 --> 01:13:44,255
Wow, that's a big fist!

694
01:14:15,497 --> 01:14:16,816
Why did you hit me?

695
01:14:44,577 --> 01:14:47,774
Where are they?

696
01:14:48,097 --> 01:14:50,167
How could you
let them escape?

697
01:14:54,017 --> 01:14:55,336
[GASPING]

698
01:14:56,017 --> 01:14:59,851
No one gets away from me!

699
01:15:01,937 --> 01:15:03,689
[###]

700
01:15:12,977 --> 01:15:15,047
Why did he save us?

701
01:15:15,217 --> 01:15:18,209
Young people make mistakes.

702
01:15:18,537 --> 01:15:22,132
But at least he
finally made good.

703
01:15:22,697 --> 01:15:26,246
Look at him!
Beaten to a pulp.

704
01:15:28,857 --> 01:15:32,008
Do you have
any last requests?

705
01:15:50,537 --> 01:15:53,290
Hey, wait!

706
01:15:53,657 --> 01:15:57,332
Why don't you write
in Chinese?
I don't understand.

707
01:16:00,617 --> 01:16:02,369
[###]

708
01:16:51,417 --> 01:16:53,373
There's no one here!

709
01:16:57,937 --> 01:17:00,497
CHINESE MEDICINE

710
01:17:13,617 --> 01:17:16,495
It's a miracle
he lasted this long.

711
01:17:17,137 --> 01:17:19,287
The herbs should help him.

712
01:17:19,537 --> 01:17:23,735
Herbal medicine can
only partly help. The key
is his own body structure.

713
01:17:23,897 --> 01:17:28,049
All his bones
and tendons are broken.

714
01:17:28,217 --> 01:17:31,050
It's amazing he's
recovering so fast.

715
01:17:31,537 --> 01:17:33,607
It can't be possible...

716
01:17:33,777 --> 01:17:35,256
Unless he's...

717
01:17:36,417 --> 01:17:37,896
[###]

718
01:17:40,297 --> 01:17:41,969
[BANDAGES SNAPPING]

719
01:18:11,057 --> 01:18:12,536
What's that smell?

720
01:18:18,097 --> 01:18:19,576
[ALL SCREAMING]

721
01:18:25,177 --> 01:18:26,929
[###]

722
01:18:45,137 --> 01:18:47,048
SING:
You mustn't smoke
while you're hurt.

723
01:18:48,497 --> 01:18:49,930
Let me handle this.

724
01:19:04,097 --> 01:19:05,496
This makes no sense.

725
01:19:16,657 --> 01:19:20,570
Who knew the Beast
could clear the chi flow

726
01:19:20,737 --> 01:19:23,205
and thus unleash
the boy's true potential?

727
01:19:23,377 --> 01:19:26,175
We should've guessed.

728
01:19:27,377 --> 01:19:30,608
He is the one!

729
01:19:30,937 --> 01:19:32,529
[###]

730
01:19:40,657 --> 01:19:42,488
Is this for real?

731
01:19:42,657 --> 01:19:45,125
You're still alive,
you turncoat?

732
01:19:45,297 --> 01:19:47,572
Kill him, men!

733
01:20:40,177 --> 01:20:41,610
What kind of move is that?

734
01:20:41,937 --> 01:20:44,326
Kids' stuff!

735
01:20:51,897 --> 01:20:53,455
[###]

736
01:21:11,057 --> 01:21:14,527
If our son were alive,
he'd be his age now.

737
01:21:14,697 --> 01:21:19,817
If he studies hard,
he could grow up to be
a doctor or lawyer.

738
01:21:19,977 --> 01:21:22,696
A stuntman, more likely!

739
01:21:31,697 --> 01:21:33,927
[DINGING]

740
01:22:17,377 --> 01:22:18,935
[THUNDER RUMBLING]

741
01:22:23,257 --> 01:22:24,770
Not bad. Let's go.

742
01:23:06,057 --> 01:23:08,013
I can even stop bullets...

743
01:23:36,897 --> 01:23:38,296
[CROAKS]

744
01:23:43,137 --> 01:23:44,365
[GRUNTS]

745
01:23:52,777 --> 01:23:54,529
[LAUGHING]

746
01:24:07,857 --> 01:24:09,575
[CROAKING]

747
01:24:15,537 --> 01:24:18,688
What? The Toad Style
of the Kwan Lun School?

748
01:24:18,857 --> 01:24:20,085
Oh, no!

749
01:25:18,817 --> 01:25:20,455
[SCREAMING]

750
01:25:39,777 --> 01:25:41,005
[BIRD SCREECHES]

751
01:26:10,937 --> 01:26:14,725
Remember the Palm move
that falls from heaven?

752
01:26:14,897 --> 01:26:17,934
That's the long lost
Buddhist Palm.

753
01:26:18,777 --> 01:26:20,130
[###]

754
01:26:51,457 --> 01:26:52,810
[SCREAMS]

755
01:27:00,417 --> 01:27:01,691
I surrender!

756
01:28:00,577 --> 01:28:01,930
What kind of move was that?

757
01:28:03,697 --> 01:28:05,767
If you want to learn,
I'll teach you.

758
01:28:14,617 --> 01:28:16,528
[CRYING]

759
01:28:17,057 --> 01:28:18,331
Master!

760
01:28:19,177 --> 01:28:20,735
[###]

761
01:29:29,177 --> 01:29:32,852
Hey! Tell him not
to put snot on the glass.

762
01:29:33,017 --> 01:29:35,531
You two, put your pants on!

763
01:29:35,697 --> 01:29:38,257
No licking
if you're not buying!

764
01:29:46,137 --> 01:29:47,490
[###]

765
01:30:41,937 --> 01:30:46,374
Kid, you have the bone
structure of a kung-fu genius.

766
01:30:46,537 --> 01:30:50,166
World peace is in your
hands. Here's the scroll
of the Buddhist Palm.

767
01:30:50,337 --> 01:30:52,612
Because it's fate,
I'll let you have it for $10.

768
01:30:52,777 --> 01:30:54,005
Wait!

769
01:30:54,417 --> 01:30:56,726
You want more...?

770
01:31:00,377 --> 01:31:02,447
[###]

771
01:35:18,097 --> 01:35:20,088
Subtitles by
SDI Media Group

